article.headline: Jacksonville St. 88, Morehead State 65
article.story: MOREHEAD, Ky. (AP) -- Courtney Bradley scored 23 points to lead Jacksonville State over Morehead State 88-65 Saturday night. Coming off a career high 25 points against Eastern Kentucky on Thursday, Bradley hit 9-of-11 shots from the field, including two 3-pointers. He also had eight rebounds. Jacksonville State (7-9, 5-5 OVC) hit nine 3-pointers in the first half to build a 47-28 halftime advantage and never looked back. Morehead State (1-15, 0-10) saw its losing streak reach 15 straight. Quentin Pryor led the Eagles with 16 while Shaun Williams added 11. B.J. Spencer finished with 17 points and Brad Peters had 11 points. Walker Russell finished with nine points but dished out 10 assists for the Gamecocks. Jacksonville State hit a season high 14 3-pointers (14 of 28).
